<h3>Full Sync with Update</h3>

<p>
Full Sync with Update is intended for comprehensive refresh operations where the
entire tenant dataset needs to be reconciled against the latest source state.
It provides broad coverage and is typically used for baseline updates or major
state alignment events.
</p>

<p>
Detailed implementation text will be added here later, including update
semantics, expected processing duration, and recommended scheduling patterns for
production tenants.
</p>

<h3>Partial Sync</h3>

<p>
Partial Sync is designed for ongoing operational cadence where teams need timely
updates without running a full reconciliation each cycle. It offers a lighter
execution profile while still keeping monitored data current.
</p>

<p>
This placeholder will be expanded with concrete examples, tradeoffs, and
guidance on where Partial Sync sits between full refresh and single-device
investigations.
</p>

<h3>Single Device Sync</h3>

<p>
Single Device Sync targets an individual serial for focused diagnostics,
validation, or post-change verification. This mode helps isolate one device
without triggering broader tenant-wide processing.
</p>

